    <keyword>time to live</keyword>
    <keyword>packet hop limit</keyword>
    <abstract>
      <t>&lt;p&gt;The use of a packet's Time to Live (TTL) (IPv4) or Hop Limit (IPv6) to verify whether the packet was originated by an adjacent node on a connected link has been used in many recent protocols.  This document generalizes this technique.  This document obsoletes Experimental RFC 3682. [STANDARDS-TRACK]&lt;/p&gt;</t>
